                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2502.12852/x7.png",
                "caption": "Figure 7:Calibration Analysis of Cross-Modal Topic Matching for InternVL 2.5 8B.Analysis:To assess the reliability of cross-modal topic matching with fewer samples than our full dataset (1004 samples per language), we randomly select 500 trajectories. We then compute performance metrics on cumulative subsets, incrementing by 50 examples at each step. The difference in performance between the full dataset and each subset is calculated to quantify the deviation at each sample size.Plot:The plot displays the average absolute spread in performance (averaged over all languages) along with the standard deviation for InternVL 2.5 8B. We restrict ourselves to a single open-weight LVLM, since the analysis yields identical results across all combinations of LVLMs and language tiers.Insights:Our analysis shows that performance stabilizes rapidly, with deviations of only about 1% observed at 1,004 instances ‚Äì same size as the subset from which the dataset was created. This indicates that reliable evaluation of cross-modal topic matching can be achieved with far fewer than 3,012 samples.",
